        <definition>typedef void(* MLAudioSoundEventCallback) (MLHandle handle, MLAudioSoundEvent event, void *context)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(MLHandle handle, MLAudioSoundEvent event, void *context)</argsstring>
        <name>MLAudioSoundEventCallback</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback to notify when a sound event has occurred. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The callback will be called on a separate thread which is non-blocking, except for calls to MLAudioDestroySound which will be blocked until the callback returns (unless the &apos;Destroy&apos; call is called from the same thread as the callback, in which case it won&apos;t be blocked). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
